---
import { markdownify } from "@/lib/utils/textConverter";
import CustomButton from "@/components/CustomButton.astro";
---

<section class="py-24 bg-white border-t border-black">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
      <div class="order-2 lg:order-1">
        <div class="bg-black/5 p-8 aspect-video flex items-center justify-center border-2 border-black relative overflow-hidden group">
            {/* Simple CSS representation of the chart concept */}
            <div class="flex items-end gap-4 h-32 w-full max-w-xs z-10">
                <div class="w-16 bg-red-500 h-full relative group-hover:opacity-50 transition-opacity">
                    <span class="absolute -top-6 left-0 text-xs font-mono font-bold">Before</span>
                </div>
                <div class="w-16 bg-green-500 h-[10%] relative">
                    <span class="absolute -top-6 left-0 text-xs font-mono font-bold">After</span>
                </div>
            </div>
             <p class="absolute bottom-2 right-2 text-[10px] text-black/40 font-mono">Real data from a client project</p>
             <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[url('/images/noise.png')] opacity-20"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="order-1 lg:order-2 space-y-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold uppercase tracking-tighter leading-none text-black">
            Featured Work: <br/><span class="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-neutral-800 to-neutral-500">The 10,000-Page Pruning Project</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed font-secondary">
          A US-based law firm was hit by a Google update, losing significant traffic. I audited their 10,000+ page site, identified 97% of it as thin or 'zombie' content, and executed a strategy to prune it down to ~300 high-value URLs. This restored crawl efficiency and stopped the bleeding.
        </p>
        <CustomButton label="Read the Full Case Study" url="/portfolio" class="btn-primary" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
